parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration/surging of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or accelerates unexpectedly
especially when slowing down or braking
the engine RPM increases suddenly
the vehicle lunges forward
the brake pedal is difficult to press
and the vehicle may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning cruise control can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control does not disengage when the brakes are applied
the vehicle surges forward
the RPM drops rapidly
and the overdrive kicks out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking gas pedal can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The gas pedal sticks and cannot be pushed down to feed gas without stomping on the pedal multiple times
usually in cold temperatures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control switch can cause unexpected acceleration or deceleration, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control switch breaks or falls off
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers may not be adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities
loss of control of the vehicle
and damage to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts can lead to delays in repairing safety-critical components, potentially putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available
manufacturer exceeded a reasonable amount of time for recall repair
and dealers confirm parts are not yet available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially putting the occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire
smoke fills the cabin
flames come from the engine
dashboard
or console area
electrical components fail
and the battery drains.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator connection can cause a loss of power to the vehicle, leaving the driver stranded and potentially trapping them inside the vehicle.
symptoms: The connection to the alternator is heavily burnt
causing a loss of power to the vehicle
and the driver is unable to exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuse box insulation can cause a fire to start under the engine compartment, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially putting the occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The insulation by the fuse box catches on fire
causing a fire to start under the engine compartment.
